# Architecture Boundaries

Controllers:
- HTTP/API input/output only; validate DTO shape; call use-cases
- no business logic, repositories, or integrations

DTOs:
- request/response shape only; API boundary only
- not domain or persistence

Commands:
- use-case input created from validated DTOs
- internal application input, not DTO, DB model, or integration payload

Use-cases:
- orchestrate one business process; enforce workflow order
- validate before side effects; check idempotency before irreversible operations
- coordinate services, repositories, integrations, mappers

Services:
- smaller business/domain logic
- no controller dependency or infrastructure leakage unless documented

Repositories:
- persistence only; DB reads/writes only
- no business decisions or external API calls

Integrations:
- external system communication only
- no business decisions or persistence logic
- no lifecycle changes unless delegated by use-case

Mappers:
- convert between DTO, Command, Domain, Persistence, Integration Payload, LLM Output
- no side effects, API calls, or DB calls

Domain types:
- documented business concepts, names, statuses, and enums only
